[By way of comparison, and to put this information in perspective, the most
recent figures from the Health Protection Agency indicate that the total
number of measles cases confirmed in England and Wales for the year to the
end of August [2010] is 292, with 67 new diagnoses in August 2010 compared
with 100 during the previous month.

Although some of the cases in August 2010 were associated with ongoing
outbreaks in traveller communities, there were also a small number of
clusters and sporadic cases outside these communities. Cases are
predominantly children under 18 years of age (73 per cent). A detailed age
breakdown of cases for 2010 to the end of August 2010 by region is
available on the HPA website at
<http://www.hpa.org.uk/web/HPAweb&HPAwebStandard/HPAweb_C/1223019390211>.

The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Northern Ireland can be
accessed at <http://healthmap.org/r/01wb>. - Mod.CP]
